comments: I learn more from the videos the professor shows than her actual lecturing. The tests, quizzes, and homeworks are completely disconnected from each other, and doing well on one doesn\'t mean you\'ll do well on any of the others. She overloads the test-prep with too much information, than lectures the class on being unable to study well. Bad teacher.

I genuinely question if she realizes this is an intro class for people filling their GenEds.

comments: While a nice person, this professor couldn\'t give a more difficult exam for a beginners level class if she tried. Study guides are very non-specific, & exams require multiple choice along with DRAWINGS (ex Volcanoes, faults). You are required to be very specific with labeling. Friend took it in summer (dif prof) and said it was a breeze. Avoid.

comments: Gina was a great professor. She was clear in her instructions and the drawings she has you do in class are really helpful for learning the concepts. Be ready to repeat those drawings on her exams. She gives partial credit, so don\'t worry if you miss a detail. Great class, awesome lab component as well. Go on the field trip to Devil\'s Lake.

comments: Dr. Seegers-Szablewski\'s lectures piqued an interest for me in geology. I eventually switched my major to geosciences and I credit her for that. Super interesting teacher. Breaks everything down to where it is understandable. Awesome professor! I don\'t remember there being a textbook. No attendance policy except for the lab portion.

comments: Gina makes it clear what you need to do to pass. Use the study guides she makes and answer all of the questions on them to study for exams. She seems intimidating at first but she\'s nice if you talk to her after class. Do every assignment and you will get extra credit.

comments: You HAVE to do the online assignments for this class because she bases what she talks about in class on what was wrong on the hw. Basically she knows that not everyone gets as excited about Geology as she does but still wants to see you do the work to pass the class. Note: I forgot to do the back side of one of my exams and she let me make it up.

comments: Show up and pay attention. Take notes from slides. HW is easy, quizzes are easy. Easy to pass if you do these. Super interesting and you can tell she loves what she\'s teaching. Almost changed my major from England to Geo, but I can\'t hack all the math that goes along with the major. Used the online learning more than my book.

comments: TAKE THIS SUMMER CLASS ONLINE! I seriously suck at this kind of stuff but I needed the credit. All of the answers for the quizzes are in the online lecture (some are kind of long) she makes slides for you to write notes along side, just keep up w/ the lectures (1 a week) and take notes. I think its 12 quizzes total and she gives you 2 chances EASY!
